hose /həʊz/

(hosing,hosed,hoses) 

1. N-COUNT A hose is a long, flexible pipe made of rubber or plastic. Water is directed through a hose in order to do things such as put out fires, clean cars, or water gardens. (橡胶或塑料制的) 水管 

例： You've left the garden hose on. 你没有关花园的水管。 

2. N-COUNT A hose is a pipe made of rubber or plastic, along which a liquid or gas flows, for example from one part of an engine to another. (用来输送液体或气体的) 软管 

例： Water in the engine compartment is sucked away by a hose. 发动机舱里的水由一条软管吸走。 

3. V-T If you hose something, you wash or water it using a hose. 用水管冲洗; 用水管浇灌 

例： We wash our cars and hose our gardens without even thinking of the water that uses. 我们冲洗汽车，浇灌花园，从没考虑过所耗费的水。 

4. N stockings, socks, and tights collectively 袜子统称

